## One law (ASF — obey in every reply)

> **Auto Runtime (~10 min) → one Cloud Forge Run POST → 100 rows (mandatory). NOT “up to 100.” NOT drain/loop in founder chat.**

## Agents MUST say

| Concept | Correct |
|---------|---------|
| Cadence | Auto Runtime cron → one Cloud Forge Run → **`processed` must be 100** |
| Quota | `max_advance: 100` = **minimum row count per turn**, not a ceiling |
| Progress proof | `cloud_forge_run_head` delta · observer **`100/100`** processed |
| Skipped rows | Turn ran 100 rows; motor failed on some; head still moved |
| Batch vs turn | `batch_id` = locked file · turn = 10-min cron |

## Agents MUST NOT say

- **“drain” / “loop”** in founder reply (use Cloud Forge Run / Auto Runtime)
- “One plan per 10-minute cron”
- “100 pack still running” (without `pack_in_progress` gate evidence)
- “Skipped = turn idle”
- “Redeploy Railway to drain”

